The paper deals with decentralised task allocation problems for multiple robots, which involves multi-agent systems and robotics (cs.MA and cs.RO). The paper proposes algorithms that leverage submodular objective functions, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also addresses the NP-hardness of the problem, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC) and control systems (cs.SY).
